Third-party academic works and software this project builds upon
================================================================================

This repository contains ORIGINAL code by the author. No third-party source
code is vendored (copied) into this repository. The items below are either
re-implemented from their published algorithms or used as external pip
dependencies.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. CAFE — Complementarity-Aware Federated Imputation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Min et al., "Cafe: Improved Federated Data Imputation by Leveraging Missing
  Data Heterogeneity" (2025).

  - src/federation/aggregation.py : the complementarity-aware (CA) aggregation
    rule is a clean re-implementation of the algorithm described in the CAFE
    paper (cosine-based complementarity of missing-mechanism fingerprints +
    power-law weighting). Algorithm/mathematics only; no CAFE source code is used.
  - src/baselines/fedice.py : a federated ICE baseline adapted from CAFE's
    ICE-style approach to the time-series tensor setting.

  The original CAFE implementation lives at sitaomin1994/federated_imputation and
  is NOT included in this repository.

  Note: the presentation slides (docs/slides.pdf) reproduce two figures from the
  CAFE paper (Fig. 1 and Fig. 2, © IEEE / the original authors), shown with
  attribution for academic illustration only. Those figures remain the property of
  their copyright holders and are not covered by this repository's MIT license.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. SAITS — Self-Attention-based Imputation for Time Series
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Du, Cote & Liu, "SAITS: Self-Attention-based Imputation for Time Series",
  Expert Systems with Applications (2023).

  - Used as the local imputation backbone via the PyPOTS library
    (https://github.com/WenjieDu/PyPOTS, BSD-3-Clause), installed as a pip
    dependency. src/models/saits_model.py is an ORIGINAL wrapper that calls
    PyPOTS's SAITS for federated parameter exchange; it does not copy SAITS code.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Federated learning baselines
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  - FedAvg  — McMahan et al. (2017)
  - FedProx — Li et al. (2020)
  - FedAdam — Reddi et al. (2021)
  Re-implemented from their respective papers in src/federation/aggregation.py.

